  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Full and Final Revelation in the Son"
      title: "God\u2019s Full and Final Revelation in the Son"
      number: 1
      content: ' Although God spoke long ago in many parts and in many ways to the
        fathers by the prophets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'in these last days he has spoken to us by a Son, whom he appointed
        heir of all things, through whom also he made the world,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'who is the radiance of his glory and the representation of his essence,
        sustaining all things by the word of power. When he had made purification
        for sins through him, he sat down at the right hand of the Majesty on high, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Son Superior to the Angels'
      title: The Son Superior to the Angels
      number: 4
      content: 'having become by so much better than the angels, by as much as he
        has inherited a more excellent name than theirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For to which of the angels did he ever say, \u201CYou are my son,
        today I have begotten you,\u201D  and again, \u201CI will be his father,
        and he will be my son\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And again, when he brings the firstborn into the world, he says,
        \u201CAnd let all the angels of God worship him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And concerning the angels he says, \u201CThe one who makes his angels
        winds, and his servants a flame of fire,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "but concerning the Son, \u201CYour throne, O God, is forever and
        ever, and the scepter of righteous is the scepter of your kingdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You have loved righteousness and hated lawlessness; because of this
        God, your God, has anointed you with the olive oil of joy more than your
        companions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And, \u201CYou, Lord, laid the foundation of the earth in the beginning,
        and the heavens are the works of your hands; "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'they will perish, but you continue, and they will all become old
        like a garment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and like a robe you will roll them up, and like a garment they will
        be changed; but you are the same, and your years will not run out.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But to which of the angels has he ever said, \u201CSit down at my
        right hand, until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Are they not all spirits engaged in special service, sent on assignment
        for the sake of those who are going to inherit salvation? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Not to Neglect Salvation'
      title: Warning Not to Neglect Salvation
      number: 1
      content: ' Because of this, it is all the more necessary that we pay attention
        to the things we have heard, lest we drift away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if the word spoken through angels was binding and every transgression
        and act of disobedience received a just penalty, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'how will we escape if we neglect so great a salvation which had its
        beginning when it was spoken through the Lord and was confirmed to us by
        those who heard, '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: The Son\u2019s Humiliation and Suffering"
      title: "The Son\u2019s Humiliation and Suffering"
      number: 4
      content: 'while God was testifying at the same time by signs and wonders and
        various miracles and distributions of the Holy Spirit according to his will. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For he did not subject to angels the world to come, about which we
        are speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But someone testified somewhere, saying, \u201CWhat is man, that
        you remember him, or the son of man, that you care for him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You made him for a short time lower than the angels; you crowned
        him with glory and honor;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'you subjected all things under his feet.  For in subjecting all things,
        he left nothing that was not subject to him. But now we do not yet see all
        things subjected to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'but we see Jesus, for a short time made lower than the angels, because
        of the suffering of death crowned with glory and honor, so that apart from
        God he might taste death on behalf of everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For it was fitting for him for whom are all things and through whom
        are all things in bringing many sons to glory to perfect the originator of
        their salvation through sufferings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For both the one who sanctifies and the ones who are sanctified are
        all from one, for which reason he is not ashamed to call them brothers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "saying, \u201CI will proclaim your name to my brothers; in the midst
        of the assembly I will sing in praise of you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And again, \u201CI will trust in him.\u201D  And again, \u201CBehold,
        I and the children God has given me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, since the children share in blood and flesh, he also in
        like manner shared in these same things, in order that through death he could
        destroy the one who has the power of death, that is, the devil, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and could set free these who through fear of death were subject to
        slavery throughout all their lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For surely he is not concerned with angels, but he is concerned with
        the descendants of Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore he was obligated to be made like his brothers in all respects,
        in order that he could become a merciful and faithful high priest in the
        things relating to God, in order to make atonement for the sins of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For in that which he himself suffered when he was tempted, he is
        able to help those who are tempted. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Superiority of Jesus to Moses'
      title: The Superiority of Jesus to Moses
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore, holy brothers, sharers in a heavenly calling, consider
        Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'who was faithful to the one who appointed him, as Moses also was
        in his household.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For this one is considered worthy of greater glory than Moses, inasmuch
        as the one who builds it has greater honor than the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For every house is built by someone, but the one who built all things
        is God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Moses was faithful in all his house as a servant, for a testimony
        to the things that would be spoken, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A Serious Warning Against Unbelief'
      title: A Serious Warning Against Unbelief
      number: 6
      content: 'but Christ was faithful as a son over his house, whose house we are,
        if we hold fast to our confidence and the hope we can be proud of. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore, just as the Holy Spirit says, \u201CToday, if you hear
        his voice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion, in the day of testing
        in the wilderness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'where your fathers tested me by trial and saw my works '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "for forty years. Therefore I was angry with this generation, and
        I said, \u2018They always go astray in their heart, and they do not know
        my ways.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As I swore in my anger, \u2018They will never enter into my rest.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Watch out, brothers, lest there be in some of you an evil, unbelieving
        heart, with the result that you fall away from the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But encourage one another day by day, as long as it is called \u201Ctoday,\u201D
        so that none of you become hardened by the deception of sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For we have become partners of Christ, if indeed we hold fast the
        beginning of our commitment steadfast until the end, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "while it is said, \u201CToday, if you hear his voice, do not harden
        your hearts as in the rebellion.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For who, when they heard it, were disobedient? Surely it was not
        all who went out from Egypt through Moses? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And with whom was he angry for forty years? Was it not with those
        who sinned, whose dead bodies fell in the wilderness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And to whom did he swear they would not enter into his rest, except
        those who were disobedient? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And so we see that they were not able to enter because of unbelief. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rest that Remains for the People of God'
      title: The Rest that Remains for the People of God
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore let us fear, while there remains a promise of entering
        into his rest, that none of you appear to fall short of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For we also have had the good news proclaimed to us, just as those
        also did, but the message they heard did not benefit them, because they were
        not united with those who heard it in faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For we who have believed enter into rest, just as he has said, \u201CAs
        I swore in my anger, \u2018They will never enter into my rest.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D 
        And yet these works have been accomplished from the foundation of the world. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For he has spoken somewhere about the seventh day in this way: \u201CAnd
        God rested on the seventh day from all his works,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and in this passage again, \u2018They will never enter into my rest.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Since therefore it remains for some to enter into it, and the ones
        to whom the good news was proclaimed previously did not enter because of
        disobedience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "again he ordains a certain day, today, speaking by David after so
        long a time, just as had been said before, \u201CToday, if you hear his voice,
        do not harden your hearts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For if Joshua had caused them to rest, he would not have spoken about
        another day after these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Consequently a sabbath rest remains for the people of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the one who has entered into his rest has also himself rested
        from his works, just as God did from his own works. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, let us make every effort to enter into that rest, in order
        that no one may fall in the same pattern of disobedience. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the word of God is living and active and sharper than any double-edged
        sword, and piercing as far as the division of soul and spirit, both joints
        and marrow, and able to judge the reflections and thoughts of the heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jesus Our Great High Priest'
      title: Jesus Our Great High Priest
      number: 13
      content: 'And no creature is hidden in the sight of him, but all things are
        naked and laid bare to the eyes of him to whom we must give our account. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, because we have a great high priest who has gone through
        the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold fast to our confession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For we do not have a high priest who is not able to sympathize with
        our weaknesses, but who has been tempted in all things in the same way, without
        sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore let us approach with confidence to the throne of grace,
        in order that we may receive mercy and find grace to help in time of need. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A High Priest Like Melchizedek'
      title: A High Priest Like Melchizedek
      number: 1
      content: ' For every high priest taken from among men is appointed on behalf
        of people in the things relating to God, in order that he can offer both
        gifts and sacrifices on behalf of sins, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'being able to deal gently with those who are ignorant and led astray,
        since he himself also is surrounded by weakness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and because of it he is obligated to offer sacrifices for sins for
        himself also, as well as for the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And someone does not take for himself the honor, but is called by
        God, just as Aaron also was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus also Christ did not glorify himself to become high priest, but
        the one who said to him, \u201CYou are my Son, today I have begotten you,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "just as also in another place he says, \u201CYou are a priest forever
        according to the order of Melchizedek,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'who in the days of his flesh offered up both prayers and supplications,
        with loud crying and tears, to the one who was able to save him from death,
        and he was heard as a result of his reverence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Although he was a son, he learned obedience from what he suffered, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and being perfected, he became the source of eternal salvation to
        all those who obey him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Advanced Teaching Hindered by Immaturity'
      title: Advanced Teaching Hindered by Immaturity
      number: 10
      content: 'being designated by God a high priest according to the order of Melchizedek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Concerning this we have much to say and it is difficult to explain,
        since you have become sluggish in hearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For indeed, although you ought to be teachers by this time, you have
        need of someone to teach you again the beginning elements of the oracles
        of God, and you have need of milk, not solid food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For everyone who partakes of milk is unacquainted with the message
        of righteousness, because he is an infant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But solid food is for the mature, who because of practice have trained
        their faculties for the distinguishing of both good and evil. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Serious Warning Against Falling Away'
      title: A Serious Warning Against Falling Away
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore, leaving behind the elementary message about Christ, let
        us move on to maturity, not laying again a foundation of repentance from
        dead works and faith in God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'teaching about baptisms and laying on of hands, and resurrection
        of the dead and eternal judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And this we will do, if God permits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For it is impossible concerning those who have once been enlightened,
        and have tasted the heavenly gift, and become sharers of the Holy Spirit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and have tasted the good word of God and the powers of the coming
        age, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and having fallen away, to renew them again to repentance, because
        they have crucified again for themselves the Son of God and held him up to
        contempt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For ground that drinks the rain that comes often upon it, and brings
        forth vegetation usable to those people for whose sake it is also cultivated,
        shares a blessing from God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if it produces thorns and thistles, it is worthless and near
        to a curse, whose end is for burning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But even if we are speaking in this way, dear friends, we are convinced
        of better things concerning you, and belonging to salvation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For God is not unjust, so as to forget your work and the love which
        you demonstrated for his name by having served the saints, and continuing
        to serve them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And we desire each one of you to demonstrate the same diligence for
        the full assurance of your hope until the end, '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: The Reliability of God\u2019s Promise"
      title: "The Reliability of God\u2019s Promise"
      number: 12
      content: 'in order that you may not be sluggish, but imitators of those who
        inherit the promises through faith and patience. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For when God made a promise to Abraham, since he had no one greater
        to swear by, he swore by himself, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "saying, \u201CSurely I will greatly bless you, and I will greatly
        multiply you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And so, by persevering, he obtained the promise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For people swear by what is greater than themselves, and the oath
        for confirmation is the end of all dispute for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the same way God, because he wanted to show even more to the heirs
        of the promise the unchangeableness of his resolve, guaranteed it with an
        oath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'in order that through two unchangeable things, in which it is impossible
        for God to lie, we who have taken refuge may have powerful encouragement
        to hold fast to the hope set before us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'which we have like an anchor of the soul, both firm and steadfast,
        and entering into the inside of the curtain, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'where Jesus, the forerunner for us, entered, because he became a
        high priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Greatness of Melchizedek'
      title: The Greatness of Melchizedek
      number: 1
      content: ' For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the most high God,
        who met Abraham as he was returning from the slaughter of the kings and blessed
        him,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "to whom also Abraham apportioned a tenth of everything\u2014in the
        first place, his name is translated \u201Cking of righteousness,\u201D and
        then also \u201Cking of Salem,\u201D that is, \u201Cking of peace\u201D; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "without father, without mother, without genealogy, having neither
        beginning of days nor end of life, but resembling the Son of God\u2014he
        remains a priest for all time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But see how great this man was, to whom Abraham the patriarch gave
        a tenth from the spoils! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And indeed those of the sons of Levi who receive the priesthood have
        a commandment to collect a tenth from the people according to the law, that
        is, from their brothers, although they are descended from Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But the one who did not trace his descent from them collected tithes
        from Abraham and blessed the one who had the promises. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now without any dispute the inferior is blessed by the more prominent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And in this case mortal men receive tithes, but in that case it is
        testified that he lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And, so to speak, even Levi, the one who receives tithes, has paid
        tithes through Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Superiority of Jesus to Melchizedek'
      title: The Superiority of Jesus to Melchizedek
      number: 10
      content: 'For he was still in the loins of his father when Melchizedek met
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Thus if perfection was through the Levitical priesthood, for on the
        basis of it the people received the law, what further need is there for another
        priest to arise according to the order of Melchizedek and not said to be
        according to the order of Aaron? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For when the priesthood changes, of necessity there is a change of
        the law also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the one about whom these things are spoken belongs to another
        tribe from which no one has officiated at the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For it is evident that our Lord is a descendant of Judah, a tribe
        with reference to which Moses said nothing concerning priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And it is still more clear, if another priest according to the likeness
        of Melchizedek arises, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'who has become a priest not according to a law of physical requirement,
        but according to the power of an indestructible life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For it is testified, \u201CYou are a priest forever according to
        the order of Melchizedek.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For on the one hand a preceding commandment is set aside because
        of its weakness and uselessness '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '(for the law made nothing perfect), but on the other hand there is
        the introduction of a better hope through which we draw near to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And by as much as this was not without an oath (for these on the
        one hand have become priests without an oath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but he with an oath by the one who said to him, \u201CThe Lord has
        sworn and will not change his mind, \u2018You are a priest forever\u2019&nbsp;\u201D), "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'by so much more Jesus has become the guarantee of a better covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And indeed many have become priests, because they were prevented
        by death from continuing in office, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'but he, because he continues forever, holds the priesthood permanently. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore also he is able to save completely those who draw near
        to God through him, because he always lives in order to intercede on their
        behalf. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For a high priest such as this indeed is fitting for us, holy, innocent,
        undefiled, separated from sinners, and having become exalted above the heavens, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'who does not need every day like the former high priests to offer
        up sacrifices for his own sins and then for the sins of the people, because
        he did this once for all when he offered up himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For the law appoints men as high priests who have weakness, but the
        statement of the oath, after the law, appoints a Son, who is made perfect
        forever. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Mediator of a New and Better Covenant'
      title: The Mediator of a New and Better Covenant
      number: 1
      content: ' Now this is the main point in what has been said: we have a high
        priest such as this, who sat down at the right hand of the throne of the
        Majesty in heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'a minister of the sanctuary and of the true tabernacle which the
        Lord set up, not man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For every high priest is appointed in order to offer both gifts and
        sacrifices; therefore it was necessary for this one also to have something
        that he offers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now if he were on earth, he would not even be a priest, because there
        are those who offer the gifts according to the law, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "who serve a sketch and shadow of the heavenly things, just as Moses
        was warned when he was about to complete the tabernacle, for he says, \u201CSee
        to it that you make everything according to the pattern which was shown to
        you on the mountain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But now he has attained a more excellent ministry, by as much as
        he is also mediator of a better covenant which has been enacted upon better
        promises. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For if that first covenant had been faultless, occasion would not
        have been sought for a second. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For in finding fault with them he says, \u201CBehold, days are coming,
        says the Lord, when I will complete a new covenant with the house of Israel
        and with the house of Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'not like the covenant which I made with their fathers on the day
        I took hold of them by my hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt, because
        they did not continue in my covenant and I disregarded them, says the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For this is the covenant that I will decree with the house of Israel
        after those days, says the Lord: I am putting my laws in their minds and
        I will write them on their hearts, and I will be their God and they will
        be my people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And they will not teach each one his fellow citizen and each one
        his brother, saying, \u2018Know the Lord,\u2019 because they will all know
        me, from the least of them to the greatest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For I will be merciful toward their wrongdoings, and I will not remember
        their sins any longer.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In calling it new, he has declared the former to be old. Now what
        is becoming obsolete and growing old is near to disappearing. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Earthly Ministry of the Old Covenant'
      title: The Earthly Ministry of the Old Covenant
      number: 1
      content: ' Now the first covenant had regulations for worship and the earthly
        sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For a tent was prepared, the first one, in which were the lampstand
        and the table and the presentation of the loaves, which is called the holy
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And after the second curtain was a tent called the holy of holies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'containing the golden incense altar and the ark of the covenant covered
        on all sides with gold, in which were a golden jar containing the manna and
        the rod of Aaron that budded and the tablets of the covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And above it were the cherubim of glory overshadowing the mercy seat,
        about which it is not now possible to speak in detail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now these things having been prepared in this way, the priests enter
        into the first tent continually as they accomplish their service, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but only the high priest enters into the second tent once a year,
        not without blood, which he offers on behalf of himself and the sins of the
        people committed in ignorance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Holy Spirit was making this clear, that the way into the holy
        place was not yet revealed, while the first tent was still in existence, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'which was a symbol for the present time, in which both the gifts
        and sacrifices which were offered were not able to perfect the worshiper
        with respect to the conscience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Heavenly Ministry of the New Covenant'
      title: The Heavenly Ministry of the New Covenant
      number: 10
      content: 'concerning instead only food and drink and different washings, regulations
        of outward things imposed until the time of setting things right. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Christ has arrived as a high priest of the good things to come.
        Through the greater and more perfect tent not made by hands, that is, not
        of this creation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and not by the blood of goats and calves, but by his own blood, he
        entered once for all into the most holy place, obtaining eternal redemption. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For if the blood of goats and bulls and the ashes of a young cow
        sprinkled on those who are defiled sanctify them for the ritual purity of
        the flesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'how much more will the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit
        offered himself without blemish to God, cleanse our consciences from dead
        works to serve the living God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And because of this, he is the mediator of a new covenant, in order
        that, because a death has taken place for the redemption of transgressions
        committed during the first covenant, those who are the called may receive
        the promise of the eternal inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For where there is a will, it is a necessity for the death of the
        one who made the will to be established. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For a will is in force concerning those who are dead, since it is
        never in force when the one who made the will is alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore not even the first covenant was ratified without blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For when every commandment had been spoken by Moses to all the people
        according to the law, he took the blood of calves with water and scarlet
        wool and hyssop and sprinkled both the scroll itself and all the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "saying, \u201CThis is the blood of the covenant that God has commanded
        for you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And likewise he sprinkled both the tabernacle and all the utensils
        of service with the blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Indeed, nearly everything is purified with blood according to the
        law, and apart from the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Therefore it was necessary for the sketches of the things in heaven
        to be purified with these sacrifices, but the heavenly things themselves
        to be purified with better sacrifices than these. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Christ did not enter into a sanctuary made by hands, a mere copy
        of the true one, but into heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of
        God on our behalf, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and not in order that he can offer himself many times, as the high
        priest enters into the sanctuary year by year with blood not his own, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'since it would have been necessary for him to suffer many times from
        the foundation of the world, but now he has appeared once at the end of the
        ages for the removal of sin by the sacrifice of himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And just as it is destined for people to die once, and after this,
        judgment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'thus also Christ, having been offered once in order to bear the sins
        of many, will appear for the second time without reference to sin to those
        who eagerly await him for salvation. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Christ\u2019s One Sacrifice for Sin"
      title: "Christ\u2019s One Sacrifice for Sin"
      number: 1
      content: ' For the law, possessing a shadow of the good things that are about
        to come, not the form of things itself, is never able year by year by means
        of the same sacrifices which they offer without interruption to make perfect
        those who draw near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For otherwise, would they not have ceased to be offered, because
        the ones who worship, having been purified once and for all, would no longer
        have any consciousness of sins? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But in them there is a reminder of sins year by year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For it is impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away
        sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Therefore, when he came into the world, he said, \u201CSacrifice
        and offering you did not want, but a body you prepared for me; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'you did not delight in whole burnt offerings and offerings for sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said, \u2018Behold, I have come\u2014 in the roll of the book
        it is written about me\u2014 to do your will, O God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When he says above, \u201CSacrifices and offerings and whole burnt
        offerings and offerings for sin you did not want, nor did you delight in,\u201D 
        which are offered according to the law, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "then he has said, \u201CBehold, I have come to do your will.\u201D 
        He takes away the first in order to establish the second, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'by which will we are made holy through the offering of the body of
        Jesus Christ once for all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And every priest stands every day serving and offering the same sacrifices
        many times, which are never able to take away sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But this one, after he had offered one sacrifice for sins for all
        time, sat down at the right hand of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'from now on waiting until his enemies are made a footstool for his
        feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For by one offering he has perfected for all time those who are made
        holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Holy Spirit also testifies to us, for after saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis is the covenant that I will decree for them after those
        days, says the Lord: I am putting my laws on their hearts, and I will write
        them on their minds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He also says, \u201CTheir sins and their lawless deeds I will never
        remember again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Hold Fast the Confession of Our Hope'
      title: Hold Fast the Confession of Our Hope
      number: 18
      content: 'Now where there is forgiveness of these, there is no longer an offering
        for sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Therefore, brothers, since we have confidence for the entrance into
        the sanctuary by the blood of Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'by the new and living way which he inaugurated for us through the
        curtain, that is, his flesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and since we have a great priest over the house of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'let us approach with a true heart in the full assurance of faith,
        our hearts sprinkled clean from an evil conscience and our bodies washed
        with pure water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Let us hold fast to the confession of our hope without wavering,
        for the one who promised is faithful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And let us think about how to stir one another up to love and good
        works, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: A Serious Warning Against Continuing Deliberate Sin'
      title: A Serious Warning Against Continuing Deliberate Sin
      number: 25
      content: 'not abandoning our meeting together, as is the habit of some, but
        encouraging each other, and by so much more as you see the day drawing near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For if we keep on sinning deliberately after receiving the knowledge
        of the truth, there no longer remains a sacrifice for sins, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'but a certain fearful expectation of judgment and a fury of fire
        that is about to consume the adversaries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Anyone who rejected the law of Moses dies without mercy on the testimony
        of two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'How much worse punishment do you think the person will be considered
        worthy of who treats with disdain the Son of God and who considers ordinary
        the blood of the covenant by which he was made holy and who insults the Spirit
        of grace? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For we know the one who said, \u201CVengeance is mine, I will repay,\u201D 
        and again, \u201CThe Lord will judge his people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It is a terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'But remember the former days in which, after you were enlightened,
        you endured a great struggle with sufferings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'sometimes being publicly exposed both to insults and to afflictions,
        and sometimes becoming sharers with those who were treated in this way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For you both sympathized with the prisoners and put up with the seizure
        of your belongings with joy because you knew that you yourselves had a better
        and permanent possession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Therefore do not throw away your confidence, which has great reward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For you have need of endurance, in order that after you have done
        the will of God, you may receive what was promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For yet \u201Ca very, very little while, and the one who is coming
        will come and will not delay. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But my righteous one will live by faith, and if he shrinks back,
        my soul is not well pleased with him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But we are not among those who shrink back to destruction, but among
        those who have faith to the preservation of our souls. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Examples of Faith in Action'
      title: Examples of Faith in Action
      number: 1
      content: ' Now faith is the realization of what is hoped for, the proof of
        things not seen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For by this the people of old were approved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By faith we understand the worlds were created by the word of God,
        in order that what is seen did not come into existence from what is visible. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'By faith Abel offered to God a greater sacrifice than Cain, by which
        he was approved that he was righteous, because God approved him for his gifts,
        and through it he still speaks, although he is dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'By faith Enoch was taken up, so that he did not experience death,
        and he was not found, because God took him up. For before his removal, he
        had been approved as having been pleasing to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now without faith it is impossible to please him, for the one who
        approaches God must believe that he exists and is a rewarder of those who
        seek him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'By faith Noah, having been warned about things not yet seen, out
        of reverence constructed an ark for the deliverance of his family, by which
        he pronounced sentence on the world and became an heir of the righteousness
        that comes by faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By faith Abraham, when he was called, obeyed to go out to a place
        that he was going to receive for an inheritance, and he went out, not knowing
        where he was going. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'By faith he lived in the land of promise as a stranger, living in
        tents with Isaac and Jacob, the fellow heirs of the same promise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For he was expecting the city that has foundations, whose architect
        and builder is God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'By faith also, with Sarah, he received the ability to procreate even
        past the normal age, because he regarded the one who had promised to be faithful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And therefore these were fathered from one man, and he being as good
        as dead, as the stars of heaven in number and like the innumerable sand by
        the shore of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'These all died in faith without receiving the promises, but seeing
        them from a distance and welcoming them, and admitting that they were strangers
        and temporary residents on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For those who say such things make clear that they are seeking a
        homeland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And if they remember that land from which they went out, they would
        have had opportunity to return. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But now they aspire to a better land, that is, a heavenly one. Therefore
        God is not ashamed of them, to be called their God, for he has prepared for
        them a city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'By faith Abraham, when he was tested, offered Isaac, and the one
        who received the promises was ready to offer his one and only son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "with reference to whom it was said, \u201CIn Isaac your descendants
        will be named,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'having reasoned that God was able even to raise him from the dead,
        from which he received him back also as a symbol. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'By faith also Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things that
        were going to happen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'By faith Jacob, as he was dying, blessed each of the sons of Joseph
        and worshiped, leaning on the top of his staff. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'By faith Joseph, as he was dying, mentioned about the exodus of the
        sons of Israel and gave instructions about his bones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'By faith Moses, when he was born, was hidden for three months by
        his parents, because they saw the child was handsome, and they were not afraid
        of the edict of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "By faith Moses, when he was grown up, refused to be called the son
        of Pharaoh\u2019s daughter, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'choosing instead to be mistreated with the people of God rather than
        to experience the transitory enjoyment of sin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'considering reproach endured for the sake of Christ greater wealth
        than the treasures of Egypt, for he was looking to the reward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'By faith he left Egypt, not fearing the anger of the king, for he
        persevered as if he saw the invisible one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'By faith he kept the Passover and the sprinkling of blood, in order
        that the one who destroyed the firstborn would not touch them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'By faith they crossed the Red Sea as if on dry land; the Egyptians,
        when they made the attempt, were drowned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'By faith the walls of Jericho fell down after they had been marched
        around for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'By faith Rahab the prostitute did not perish with those who were
        disobedient, because she welcomed the spies in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And what more shall I say? For time would fail me to tell about Gideon,
        Barak, Samson, Jephthah, David, and Samuel and the prophets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'who through faith conquered kingdoms, accomplished justice, obtained
        what was promised, shut the mouths of lions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'extinguished the effectiveness of fire, escaped the edge of the sword,
        were made strong from weakness, became mighty in battle, put to flight enemy
        battle lines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Women received back their dead by resurrection. But others were tortured,
        not accepting release, in order that they might gain a better resurrection. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And others experienced mocking and flogging, and in addition bonds
        and imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'They were stoned, they were sawed in two, they died by murder with
        a sword, they wandered about in sheepskins, in goatskins, impoverished, afflicted,
        mistreated, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'of whom the world was not worthy, wandering about on deserts and
        mountains and in caves and in holes in the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And although they all were approved through their faith, they did
        not receive what was promised, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'because God had provided something better for us, so that they would
        not be made perfect without us. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Example of Jesus\u2019 Suffering"
      title: "The Example of Jesus\u2019 Suffering"
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore, since we also have such a great cloud of witnesses surrounding
        us, putting aside every weight and the sin that so easily ensnares us, let
        us run with patient endurance the race that has been set before us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'fixing our eyes on Jesus, the originator and perfecter of faith,
        who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, disregarding the
        shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For consider the one who endured such hostility by sinners against
        himself, so that you will not grow weary in your souls and give up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You have not yet resisted to the point of shedding your blood as
        you struggle against sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And have you completely forgotten the exhortation which instructs
        you as sons? \u201CMy son, do not make light of the Lord\u2019s discipline,
        or give up when you are corrected by him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord disciplines the one whom he loves, and punishes every
        son whom he accepts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Endure it for discipline. God is dealing with you as sons. For what
        son is there whom a father does not discipline? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if you are without discipline, in which all legitimate sons have
        become participants, then you are illegitimate and not sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Furthermore, we have had our earthly fathers who disciplined us,
        and we respected them. Will we not much rather subject ourselves to the Father
        of spirits and live? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For they disciplined us for a few days according to what seemed appropriate
        to them, but he does so for our benefit, in order that we can have a share
        in his holiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: A Serious Warning Against Refusing God'
      title: A Serious Warning Against Refusing God
      number: 11
      content: 'Now all discipline seems for the moment not to be joyful but painful,
        but later it yields the peaceful fruit of righteousness for those who are
        trained by it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore strengthen your slackened hands and your weakened knees, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and make straight paths for your feet, so that what is lame will
        not be dislocated, but rather be healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Pursue peace with everyone, and holiness, without which no one will
        see the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Take care that no one falls short of the grace of God; that no one
        growing up like a root of bitterness causes trouble, and by it many become
        defiled; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'that no one be a sexually immoral or totally worldly person like
        Esau, who for one meal traded his own birthright. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For you know that also afterwards, when he wanted to inherit the
        blessing, he was rejected, because he did not find an occasion for repentance,
        although he sought it with tears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For you have not come to something that can be touched, and to a
        burning fire, and to darkness, and to gloom, and to a whirlwind, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and to the noise of a trumpet, and to the sound of words which those
        who heard begged that not another word be spoken to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For they could not endure what was commanded: \u201CIf even an animal
        touches the mountain, it must be stoned.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the spectacle was so terrifying that Moses said, \u201CI am terrified
        and trembling.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But you have come to Mount Zion, and to the city of the living God,
        to the heavenly Jerusalem, and to tens of thousands of angels, to the festal
        gathering '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and assembly of the firstborn who are enrolled in heaven, and to
        God the judge of all, and to the spirits of righteous people made perfect, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and to Jesus, the mediator of a new covenant, and to the sprinkled
        blood that speaks better than Abel\u2019s does. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Watch out that you do not refuse the one who is speaking! For if
        those did not escape when they refused the one who warned them on earth,
        much less will we escape, if we reject the one who warns from heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "whose voice shook the earth at that time, but now he has promised,
        saying, \u201CYet once more I will shake not only the earth but also heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Now the phrase \u201Cyet once more\u201D indicates the removal of
        what is shaken, namely, things that have been created, in order that the
        things that are not shaken may remain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore, since we are receiving an unshakable kingdom, let us be
        thankful, through which let us serve God acceptably, with awe and reverence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For indeed our God is a consuming fire. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Concluding Ethical Instructions'
      title: Concluding Ethical Instructions
      number: 1
      content: ' Brotherly love must continue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Do not neglect hospitality, because through this some have received
        angels as guests without knowing it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Remember the prisoners, as though you were fellow-prisoners; remember
        the mistreated, as though you yourselves also are being mistreated in the
        body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Marriage must be held in honor by all, and the marriage bed be undefiled,
        because God will judge sexually immoral people and adulterers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Your lifestyle must be free from the love of money, being content
        with what you have. For he himself has said, \u201CI will never desert you,
        and I will never abandon you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So then, we can say with confidence, \u201CThe Lord is my helper,
        I will not be afraid.  What will man do to me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember your leaders, who spoke the word of God to you; considering
        the outcome of their way of life, imitate their faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today and forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not be carried away by various and strange teachings, for it is
        good for the heart to be strengthened by grace, not by foods by which those
        who participate have not benefited. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We have an altar from which those who serve in the tabernacle do
        not have the right to eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the bodies of those animals whose blood is brought into the sanctuary
        by the high priest for sins are burned up outside the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore Jesus also suffered outside the gate, in order that he
        might sanctify the people by his own blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So we must go out to him outside the camp, bearing his reproach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For here we do not have a permanent city, but we seek the city that
        is to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore through him let us offer up a sacrifice of praise continually
        to God, that is, the fruit of lips that confess his name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And do not neglect doing good and generosity, for God is pleased
        with such sacrifices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Obey your leaders and submit to them, for they keep watch over your
        souls as those who will give an account, so that they can do this with joy
        and not with groaning, for this would be unprofitable for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Pray for us, for we are convinced that we have a good conscience,
        and want to conduct ourselves commendably in every way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Benediction'
      title: Benediction
      number: 19
      content: 'And I especially urge you to do this, so that I may be restored to
        you more quickly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now may the God of peace, who brought up from the dead our Lord Jesus,
        the great shepherd of the sheep, by the blood of the eternal covenant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Conclusion'
      title: Conclusion
      number: 21
      content: 'equip you with every good thing to do his will, carrying out in us
        what is pleasing before him through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory forever.
        Amen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now I urge you, brothers, bear with my word of exhortation, for indeed
        I have written to you briefly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Know that our brother Timothy has been released, with whom I will
        see you, if he comes quickly enough. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Greet all your leaders and all the saints. Those from Italy greet
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Grace be with all of you. '
      comments: []
